questions: Explain the difference between a list and a tuple in Python. When would you use each?

answers: In python, list is mutable, values can be changed so it is used for dynamic data. Tuple is immutable and used for fixed data.
Inheritance allows to acquire properties from another. Polymorphism lets subclass modify or define methods
abstract has both abstract and concrete methods. interface only has abstract methods
